__NOTOC__ fixed '''Ceil''' (fixed ''value'')
==Usage== Rounds the specified value to the highest whole number.
===Return value=== The value after rounding, as a fixed-point number.
==Custom function== {{note|The following is a non-native implementation of the function, for versions of GZDoom older than 2.4.0.}} Map a fixed point value to the highest whole number. [[Functions|function]] [[Data_types#Integer|int]] ceil ([[Data_types#Integer|int]] x) { return (x + 65535) & 0xFFFF0000; }
